# Medical Chatbot with Machine Learning

## Overview
This project explores the design of a medical chatbot supported by machine learning and natural language processing techniques.
The focus is on demonstrating classification, intent recognition, and conversational support concepts.

## Objectives
- Process and prepare text data
- Build a model for intent or response prediction
- Evaluate model performance
- Present findings clearly for a non-technical audience

## Tools and Technologies
- Python
- NLP libraries
- Scikit-learn
- Pandas
- Jupyter Notebook

## Dataset
The project uses text-based input data relevant to healthcare or symptom-based interactions. 
Additional dataset details will be documented in the final version.

## Methods
- Text preprocessing
- Tokenization
- Feature extraction
- Machine learning model training
- Evaluation and interpretation

## Results
This draft project demonstrates the workflow for developing a machine learning-supported chatbot. 
Detailed results and examples will be added as the project is finalized.

